AML is a language that defines events that
occur in time, and it uses two fundamental temporal abstractions --
concurrency and sequentiality.  The AML "chord" operator is really a
generalized concurrency notation, and AML sequences define events that
occur one after another.  AML allows mixing of these two very
fundamental notions in a structured way. 


